Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.30,0:00:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're from Mistral? That place sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.99,0:00:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it has great food and a ton of hot chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been almost six months since the armistice, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.41,0:01:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta thank my lucky stars that I'm still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.65,0:01:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I win.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.54,0:01:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.65,0:01:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.75,0:01:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to get up, missy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.65,0:01:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll share my booty with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.81,0:01:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caramel!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.43,0:01:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't accept something so expensive...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.47,0:01:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Sergeant!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.01,0:01:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.15,0:01:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you don't give the trumpeters a hard time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.19,0:01:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make sure you hear the withdrawal signal loud and clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.10,0:01:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't see too many new recruits nowadays, what with the draft being over and all...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a volunteer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.78,0:01:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I want to learn music!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.01,0:01:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, honesty's the best policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.70,0:01:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, missy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.42,0:01:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name, private?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.51,0:01:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.45,0:01:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorami Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.26,0:02:08.17,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\pos(951,432)\fad(0,2500)\fndearJoe 5 CASUAL\fs70}Sound of the Skies
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.90,0:02:22.48,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Does the light of the sky reach your heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.91,0:02:32.37,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}The melody we dreamed of was serene.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.61,0:02:37.47,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Even though the dream is so far from you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.58,0:02:42.49,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Try to recall that gentle voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.59,0:02:55.32,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Someone's singing a graceful chord for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:59.67,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}May the sound of the skies resound,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.77,0:03:04.75,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}overcoming sadness with all its might.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.75,0:03:15.36,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Only the real world reflects in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:24.67,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Don't let your tears form any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.77,0:03:29.96,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}Within the overflowing light,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.07,0:03:36.94,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\org(0,0)\fad(120,120)}may you play out the morrow.
